  "title": "Question on the page \"Routing and urls\"",
  "body": "Hi! I have a documentation issue on InstantSearch.js. I could not find what I was looking for on the page \"[Routing and urls](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/guides/routing.html)\".\r\n\r\nMy attributeName is on an object, for exemple 'merchant.name'.\r\nThe widget work great with `attributeName: 'merchant.name',` but when i would like change the routing, it seems not possible.\r\n\r\nWhen i refine, the url look like : `?refinementList%5Bmerchant.name%5D%5B0%5D=aaaaaaaaa`\r\n\r\nSo i try  `uiState.refinementList.merchant.name` or `uiState.refinementList.[merchant.name][0]` or `uiState.refinementList.[merchant.name]` or `uiState.refinementList['merchant.name']`  but it generate errors.\r\n\r\nDo you have any idea, how i could do this ?\r\n\r\nThanks",
